        <!-- Project Context -->
        <section class="project-section">
            <p> <strong>Taxes and Tenacity (2023)</strong> Created by a duo during an 2 week gamejam, this
                roguelite game weaves RPG elements with a life-and-tax system. In this world, the player embarks
                on dungeon expeditions to collect gold from defeated monsters, facing a looming tax deadline.
                Successfully paying
                your taxes, means earning extra lives; failure leads to losing them all. With each dive, both the stakes
                and the
                character's capabilities escalate.
                <br><br>
                As the <Strong> Game Designer, Programmer, and Animator</Strong>, I developed the core mechanics, including player and
                camera movement, character stats, enemy AI, and the overarching
                game manager. Designing the attack patterns for enemies and the player's moveset was a particular
                challenge, allowing for a dynamic combat experience. Balancing the economy, players can invest their
                gold in permanent stat upgrades or temporary boosts, adding a strategic layer to each run. My partner
                contributed by crafting intricate levels, the map that connects them, and devising the
                final boss’s attack sequences.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Things I Learned -->
        <section class="project-section learned-things">
            <h2>Things I Learned</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Data management across scenes</li>
                <li>Implemented state machines for both AI behavior, player controls and animation</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

